        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 5:04PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 504 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles northeast of Evans, or 6 miles east of Greeley, moving
northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Southeastern Greeley, Evans, Kersey, Gill, Barnesville, Garden
City and Lower Latham Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
